{
  "text": ". The AIT-and CNAD-loaded MSNP release studies performed revealed that the maximum concentrations detected in solution as a result of being released from 2 mg ml 21 of loaded MSNPs were 362.7 mg l 21 for AIT and 34.8 mg l [CITATION_1] for CNAD. To directly compare the killing efficiencies of AIT and CNAD in free form versus encapsulated in pores of MSNPs, when used at the same concentrations, E. coli suspensions grown and adjusted as described above were each incubated with the following treatments for 18 h at 328C with 120 r.p.m. agitation: (i) no treatment (negative control), (ii) 362.7 mg l 21 AIT, (iii) 2 mg ml 21 AIT-loaded MSNPs, (iv) 1 mg ml [CITATION_2] AIT-loaded MSNPs, (v) 34.8 mg l",
